complexity
## Location
src/tools/bash/mod.rs:319-401
## Violation
`execute_bash` is 83 lines, branches on `run_in_background`, then on `#[cfg(windows)]`, then constructs output, truncates, and sets `is_error` from exit status. SRP violation: argument extraction, OS-specific spawn, output assembly, truncation, error-mapping all in one function. Cyclomatic ~12.

Quoted (mod.rs:319-401, abridged):
```
pub fn execute_bash(args: &HashMap<String, Value>) -> (String, bool) {
    let Some(command) = args.get("command")... else { ... };
    if let Err(msg) = validate_command(command) { ... }
    let run_in_background = args.get("run_in_background")...
    if run_in_background { ... } else {
        #[cfg(windows)] let output = { ... };
        #[cfg(not(windows))] let output = { ... };
        match output { Ok(output) => { ... if result.len() > 50000 { ... } ... } }
    }
}
```
## Mandated refactor
1. Split: `parse_bash_args`, `spawn_sync`, `spawn_async`, `render_output`.
2. Move OS-specific spawn into `platform::spawn` with cfg at definition site.
3. Replace 50_000 magic literal with named const.
